# BRANCH NAMING CONVENTIONS

## FORMAT
```
<type>/<scope>-<description>
```

## TYPES
`feat` | `fix` | `docs` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `build` | `chore` | `revert`

## SCOPES (Jmix/Vaadin)
`jmix` | `vaadin` | `entity` | `view` | `service` | `security` | `liquibase` | `ui` | `api` | `db` | `config` | `test` | `ci` | `deps`

## RULES
- Lowercase, kebab-case (hyphens)
- Max 50 chars (excluding type/scope prefix)
- Descriptive: what the branch does
- No special characters except hyphens
- No trailing slashes or dots

## EXAMPLES
```
feat/vaadin-add-login-form
fix/jmix-resolve-datamanager-npe
refactor/service-extract-payment-logic
docs/update-setup-guide
test/add-integration-tests
chore/update-dependencies
build/configure-gradle-cache
ci/add-commitlint-check
```

## PROHIBITIONS
❌ Uppercase | Spaces | Underscores | Special chars | Vague names | Periods | Trailing slashes
❌ `feature/`, `bugfix/`, `hotfix/` (use `feat/`, `fix/` instead)
❌ `master`, `main`, `develop` (protected branches)

## VALIDATION
- Regex: `^(feat|fix|docs|refactor|perf|test|build|chore|revert)/(jmix|vaadin|entity|view|service|security|liquibase|ui|api|db|config|test|ci|deps)-[a-z0-9-]+$`
- Enforced in GitHub Actions
- Blocks merge if invalid
